The evidence with the title '1938 and 2015: only the Names are different | realclearpolitics ' says Jul 21, 2015  ... We say that evil is dark . But this metaphor is imprecise. Evil is actually intensely bright, so painfully bright that people look away from it. Many even deny its existence. Why? Because once people acknowledge evil's existence, they know they have to confront it. And most people prefer not to confront evil. 
